race.comment: DR. ANGELO (7) doesn't have the best strike-rate. Hit the board with a minor placing last time when third (25.20) at this track. Has a good record here at this journey. Makes plenty of appeal. SHAUN LEE ROSE (4) was safely held in tougher company last start after drifting back at this track, but prior to that won comfortably by 6 lengths at this track (24.77) beating Boo Boo Giblet in a Grade 5 on October 22. Bold showing expected. DERMOTT ROSE (3) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fourth (24.99) at this track. Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from five starts. A big run wouldn't surprise. JUMBUK JOZEF (6) should be thereabouts. Something for the Multiples: SPICY SIREN (2) DR. ANGELO (7)
